title: ROADRUNNER UNITED - The All-Star Session [2005] [192 kbps]
description:
Roadrunner United was a project organized by the heavy metal record label Roadrunner Records to celebrate its 25th anniversary. It culminated in an album released worldwide on October 11, 2005, entitled The All-Star Sessions. Four "team captains" were chosen to lead 57 artists from 45 past and present Roadrunner bands, and produce and oversee the album&#039;s 18 tracks: Joey Jordison of Slipknot and Murderdolls Matt Heafy of Trivium, Dino Cazares of Asesino and Divine Heresy and formerly of Brujeria, and Fear Factory; and Robert Flynn of Machine Head and formerly of Vio-lence and Forbidden.
